#Calculating RMSE
rmse = sqrt(mean((dat3$Creditex - pred)^2))
## Warning in dat3$Creditex - pred: longer object length is not a multiple of
## shorter object length

## [1] NA
#Calculating Rsquared manually
y = dat3[,c("Creditex")]
R.squared = 1 - sum((y-pred)^2)/sum((y-mean(y))^2)
## Warning in mean.default(y): argument is not numeric or logical: returning NA
print(R.squared)
## [1] -Inf
#Calculating Adj. Rsquared manually
n = dim(dat3)[1]
p = dim(summary(stepBIC)$coeff)[1] - 1
adj.r.squared = 1 - (1 - R.squared) * ((n - 1)/(n-p-1))
print(adj.r.squared)
